==English==

===Etymology===
from {{OF.}} ''licence'', from {{L.}} ''[[licentia]]''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{cattag|Commonwealth English}} Standard spelling of the noun form of [[license]].

====Usage notes====
This spelling is always considered incorrect in the United States.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|licenc|ing}}

# {{cattag|Commonwealth English}} Alternative spelling of license, generally considered to be erroneous.  The verb form should normally be spelt as [[license]].

====Usage notes====
This spelling is always considered incorrect in the United States.

===Derived terms===
* [[artistic licence]]
* [[off-licence]]
* [[licenced]] (Sometimes used incorrectly)
* [[licentiate]]
* [[licentious]]
* [[poetic licence]]
* [[road fund licence]]

